c: 4
v: 119
t: "I will surely lead them astray and surely engross them in vain desires (superstitious fancies and false conceptions); and I will surely command them, and they will surely slit the ears of cattle (to mark them out as meant for their idols and as forbidden to themselves to eat, thus making a lawful thing unlawful); and also I will surely command them and they will surely alter God’s creation.\" Whoever takes Satan for a confidant and guardian instead of God has indeed suffered a manifest loss"